    <!--
    use Type="Replace" or "Merge" and specify the path to the 
    Object you want to modify, then put the modified Object in the ModOp body, 
    you can modify any field of the Object this way, and you can also add 
    new fields if needed, just make sure the GUID of the Object is correct 
    and matches the one in the game data, otherwise it will create a new 
    Object instead of modifying the existing one

    Old style vs new style:
    <ModOp Type="Merge" GUID="5473" Path="Values/Object">
    <ModOp Merge="@5473/Object">
        <Object>
            <Name>New Name</Name>
        </Object>
    </ModOp>

    -->


